Appsterdam is a volunteer-run, non-profit community which organizes events for App Makers, by App Makers. We provide infrastructure to support the app ecosystem with weekly lectures, weekly bar meetups, peer support, tech events and more. Our goal is to bring people together, no matter what background or skill level you possess.

Cross-pollination is the key to innovation.

At any of our events you can meet a developer, a designer, an accountant, a marketeer, or even a lawyer. Who knows? Maybe the person you meet is the one who will raise your project to a higher level or change your life for the better.

Stichting Appsterdam is a non-profit meta-organization that provides common ground for all App Makers, regardless of platform, occupation, or business model, in Amsterdam and beyond. An App Maker is a person or organization who contributes to the creation of apps, be they engineers, designers, businessmen, lawyers, or marketeers. An app is a piece of software that transforms its hardware to provide a complete productized experience. Appsterdam is the world’s most advanced infrastructure for App Makers, by App Makers. Our goal is to bring App Makers together, and our mission is to support the interests of App Makers worldwide. We have built Appsterdam, the world capital of apps, to establish a center of gravity to our industry, and to provide a place in the world where all App Makers can gather. The intent is to build a structured ecosystem of cooperating App Makers with Amsterdam as its center. We help App Makers understand and practice community values, such as craftsmanship, quality, diversity, cooperation, and professionalism.

For inquiries, please write to info@appsterdam.rs


Appsterdam acquired the ANBI-status. An ‘ANBI’ is a Dutch non-profit public welfare organization. Donations to Appsterdam are tax deductible. You can find Appsterdam in the ANBI search tool. Here is a capture of the search tool screen that you can add to your tax declaration. Appsterdam has to comply with the associated ANBI regulation, which includes transparency. GDG Zinder est une communauté de développeurs, de concepteurs et de passionnés de la technologie dans la ville de Zinder. Elle fait partie du programme Google Developer Groups (GDG), qui est un réseau mondial de communautés axées sur les technologies et les plateformes Google et sur d'autres sujets liés à la technologie.

La communauté a été fondée en 2023 dans le but de rassembler les passionnés de technologie locaux pour apprendre, partager des connaissances, collaborer sur des projets et créer un réseau de soutien pour les développeurs en herbe (débutants) à Zinder en organisant régulièrement des ateliers et des événements.

GDG Zinder organise une variété d'événements tout au long de l'année, y compris des formations en virtuel ou en présentiel, des hackathons, séminaires ...Ces événements sont conçus pour éduquer les membres de cette communauté sur divers aspects de la technologie et favoriser la collaboration entre les membres afin de s'auto-suffire. La communauté fournit également une plateforme permettant aux développeurs de présenter leurs projets et de recevoir des commentaires de la part des autres membres.

L'un des aspects uniques de GDG Zinder est l'accent mis sur la promotion de la diversité et de l'inclusion dans la technologie. La communauté cherche activement à impliquer et à soutenir les femmes, les étudiants, et les autres groupes sous-représentés dans la technologie. Pour ce faire, elle crée un environnement sûr et accueillant pour tous les membres et organise des événements spécifiquement adaptés aux besoins de ces groupes.

Dans l'ensemble, GDG Zinder est un élément important de l'écosystème technologique de Zinder. Il offre aux développeurs locaux et aux passionnés de technologie une plateforme qui leur permet de se connecter, d'apprendre et de collaborer pour une autosuffisance.

Appsterdam is a volunteer-run, non-profit community which organizes events for App Makers, by App Makers. We provide infrastructure to support the app ecosystem with weekly lectures, weekly bar meetups, peer support, tech events and more. Our goal is to bring people together, no matter what background or skill level you possess.

Cross-pollination is the key to innovation.

At any of our events you can meet a developer, a designer, an accountant, a marketeer, or even a lawyer. Who knows? Maybe the person you meet is the one who will raise your project to a higher level or change your life for the better.

Stichting Appsterdam is a non-profit meta-organization that provides common ground for all App Makers, regardless of platform, occupation, or business model, in Amsterdam and beyond. An App Maker is a person or organization who contributes to the creation of apps, be they engineers, designers, businessmen, lawyers, or marketeers. An app is a piece of software that transforms its hardware to provide a complete productized experience. Appsterdam is the world’s most advanced infrastructure for App Makers, by App Makers. Our goal is to bring App Makers together, and our mission is to support the interests of App Makers worldwide. We have built Appsterdam, the world capital of apps, to establish a center of gravity to our industry, and to provide a place in the world where all App Makers can gather. The intent is to build a structured ecosystem of cooperating App Makers with Amsterdam as its center. We help App Makers understand and practice community values, such as craftsmanship, quality, diversity, cooperation, and professionalism.

For inquiries, please write to info@appsterdam.rs


Appsterdam acquired the ANBI-status. An ‘ANBI’ is a Dutch non-profit public welfare organization. Donations to Appsterdam are tax deductible. You can find Appsterdam in the ANBI search tool. Appsterdam is a volunteer-run, non-profit community which organizes events for App Makers, by App Makers. We provide infrastructure to support the app ecosystem with weekly lectures, weekly bar meetups, peer support, tech events and more. Our goal is to bring people together, no matter what background or skill level you possess.

Cross-pollination is the key to innovation.

At any of our events you can meet a developer, a designer, an accountant, a marketeer, or even a lawyer. Who knows? Maybe the person you meet is the one who will raise your project to a higher level or change your life for the better.

Stichting Appsterdam is a non-profit meta-organization that provides common ground for all App Makers, regardless of platform, occupation, or business model, in Amsterdam and beyond. An App Maker is a person or organization who contributes to the creation of apps, be they engineers, designers, businessmen, lawyers, or marketeers. An app is a piece of software that transforms its hardware to provide a complete productized experience. Appsterdam is the world’s most advanced infrastructure for App Makers, by App Makers. Our goal is to bring App Makers together, and our mission is to support the interests of App Makers worldwide. We have built Appsterdam, the world capital of apps, to establish a center of gravity to our industry, and to provide a place in the world where all App Makers can gather. The intent is to build a structured ecosystem of cooperating App Makers with Amsterdam as its center. We help App Makers understand and practice community values, such as craftsmanship, quality, diversity, cooperation, and professionalism.

For inquiries, please write to info@appsterdam.rs

GDG Melbourne is for anyone interested in developing and learning about Android and other exciting Google related technologies. We cover such topics as Kotlin, Java, Flutter, Firebase, Machine Learning, VR & AR, Google Assistant, Wearables and IoT.

Regardless of your skill level or experience, it's a fun and open environment, so we'd love to have you come along! Some of the events we hold are:

• Monthly Meetups

We hold monthly meetups in the Melbourne CBD, on the last Wednesday of each month. We typically have two lightning talks coupled with a longer presentation. Each meetup also includes time to talk and network, a summary of new releases and local developer introductions. Catering is provided.

• Hack Nights

Hack nights are hosted in a casual environment to allow you to network with like minded developers and work on your own projects. Experts, colleagues and peers are on hand to help you out with problems and to collaborate on projects. Catering is provided.

• Special events

Typically one-off events such as a Google I/O Extended (a recap of the event and announcements), Study Jams (free training sessions), DevFest (one day conference) or social events like Christmas parties.

Learn more on our website

Keep up to date on all thing GDG Melbourne or join the discussions on:

• Slack

Appsterdam is a volunteer-run, non-profit community which organizes events for App Makers, by App Makers. We provide infrastructure to support the app ecosystem with weekly lectures, weekly bar meetups, peer support, tech events and more. Our goal is to bring people together, no matter what background or skill level you possess.

Cross-pollination is the key to innovation.

At any of our events you can meet a developer, a designer, an accountant, a marketeer, or even a lawyer. Who knows? Maybe the person you meet is the one who will raise your project to a higher level or change your life for the better.

Stichting Appsterdam is a non-profit meta-organization that provides common ground for all App Makers, regardless of platform, occupation, or business model, in Amsterdam and beyond. An App Maker is a person or organization who contributes to the creation of apps, be they engineers, designers, businessmen, lawyers, or marketeers. An app is a piece of software that transforms its hardware to provide a complete productized experience. Appsterdam is the world’s most advanced infrastructure for App Makers, by App Makers. Our goal is to bring App Makers together, and our mission is to support the interests of App Makers worldwide. We have built Appsterdam, the world capital of apps, to establish a center of gravity to our industry, and to provide a place in the world where all App Makers can gather. The intent is to build a structured ecosystem of cooperating App Makers with Amsterdam as its center. We help App Makers understand and practice community values, such as craftsmanship, quality, diversity, cooperation, and professionalism.

For inquiries, please write to info@appsterdam.rs


Appsterdam acquired the ANBI-status. An ‘ANBI’ is a Dutch non-profit public welfare organization. Donations to Appsterdam are tax deductible. You can find Appsterdam in the ANBI search tool. Here is a capture of the search tool screen that you can add to your tax declaration. Appsterdam has to comply with the associated ANBI regulation, which includes transparency. In this section you can find the required information. If you have any inquiries with respect to the ANBI status, please write to legal@appsterdam.rs.
